  <li id="comment-33926" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/09107035443117362865" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Susan.....</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/03/this-is-important/#comment-33926"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-03-08T15:15:32-05:00">Thursday, March 8, 2012 at 3:15 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I have been making overnight yeast waffles for years and I have good days and bad days even with the same recipe. I find that even overnight the weather can change the dough structure so if my first one is not as crisp as I would like I mix in a couple tablespoons of cornstarch. Seems to do the trick and the batch is saved. I love the addition of buckwheat.  Congratulations on your upcoming Motherhood!</p>
    </div>

