  <li id="comment-33938" class="comment even thread-even depth-1">
    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/02472802098557216513" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Christina Wilsdon</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/03/this-is-important/#comment-33938"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-03-08T17:00:17-05:00">Thursday, March 8, 2012 at 5:00 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>Congratulations on Baby&#8211;enjoy the accolades and warmth, even from strangers, that comes with being with child; I know I did. </p>
<p>On waffle irons&#8211;Cuisinart makes (made?) a fun one that produces a row of four-inch-long, &#8220;stick&#8221; shaped waffles&#8211;they puff up beautifully so they aren&#39;t skinny, as that sounds, they&#39;re more like what a good puffy doughnut that has been unrolled and put straight would be like&#8211;which are fun and easy to eat using your fingers (and your mouth of course 🙂 and to dip in maple syrup, and are REALLY delightful to serve to kids because you can cook a batch, break them apart, serve them to the crowd, and cook a second batch while the first gets devoured without squabbling amongst the urchins.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="reply">
      <a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-33938' data-commentid="33938" data-postid="427" data-belowelement="comment-33938" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Christina Wilsdon" aria-label='Reply to Christina Wilsdon'>Reply</a>    </div>
