<p>On waffle irons&#8211;Cuisinart makes (made?) a fun one that produces a row of four-inch-long, &#8220;stick&#8221; shaped waffles&#8211;they puff up beautifully so they aren&#39;t skinny, as that sounds, they&#39;re more like what a good puffy doughnut that has been unrolled and put straight would be like&#8211;which are fun and easy to eat using your fingers (and your mouth of course 🙂 and to dip in maple syrup, and are REALLY delightful to serve to kids because you can cook a batch, break them apart, serve them to the crowd, and cook a second batch while the first gets devoured without squabbling amongst the urchins.</p>
