    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I&#39;ve never understood the fuss about waffles &#8212; the one time I had them, made by a friend in her heart-shaped waffle iron, served with strawberries and whipped cream&#8230; I thought, &#39;Meh. Dry.&#39; So I stayed faithful to my pancakes (which I make with half wholewheat flour and eat with LOTS of yogurt and homemade maple-berry syrup ).</p>
<p>But now that I&#39;ve read this post and all the comments&#8230; somehow, &#39;Get a waffle iron&#39; has made it onto my to-do list. That one time must have been an aberration. I can&#39;t not try again.</p>
<p>And huge congratulations, Molly, on what&#39;s cooking under your shirt. I follow your blog with bated breath, and I&#39;m so excited for you.</p>
