    <header class="comment--meta">
      <div class="vcard"><cite class="comment-author fn"><a href="https://www.blogger.com/profile/18011427378875918113" class="url" rel="ugc external nofollow">Unknown</a></cite></div>
      <a href="https://orangette.net/2012/03/this-is-important/#comment-34003"><time class="comment-time" datetime="2012-03-13T17:39:42-04:00">Tuesday, March 13, 2012 at 5:39 pm</time></a>    </header>

    
    <div class="comment--content">
      <p>I love Marion Cunningham&#39;s Yeasted Waffles, too.  My son and I make them with all whole wheat flour (pastry or regular), so we will totally try the buckwheat innovation.  BTW, we find that we do not actually have to mix the batter smooth before letting it rest overnight.  Many degrees of lumpiness have magically disappeared by morning, so feel free just to mix as long as you like.  It will be a great job for your little one to take on!  All the best to you and Brandon and baby-to-be.</p>
    </div>

